###Setting up a proportion

Corresponding sides of similar triangles are proportional, so we can set up and solve a proportion:

$\dfrac{\blueE{AD}}{AC}=\dfrac{DE}{CB}$

We picked side $\blueE{\overline{AD}}$ because we need to find its length.

We picked side $\overline{AC}$ because it corresponds to side $\blueE{\overline{AD}}$.

Then we picked another pair of corresponding sides whose lengths we already knew.

$\begin{array}{rcl}
&\triangle AED
\\
{\text{short} \atop \text{leg}}
&\overbrace{\underbrace{\!\!\!\!\!\left\{ 
\dfrac{\blueE{AD}}{AC}=\dfrac{DE}{CB}
\right\}\!\!\!\!\!}}
&{\text{long} \atop \text{leg}}
\\
&\triangle ABC
\end{array}$

